This paper is about improving the accuracy of Winograd convolution for deep neural networks. The paper discusses methods for reducing floating point error and improving the numerical accuracy of the algorithm. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and scientific computing (cs.SC).
